# Tauri Architecture Patterns

> **Scope**: Applies when editing Rust files in the Tauri backend root (not in audio/, whisper_engine/, or lifecycle/ subdirectories)

## Command Pattern (Frontend → Rust)

```rust
#[tauri::command]
async fn my_command<R: Runtime>(
    app: AppHandle<R>,
    arg: String
) -> Result<String, String> {
    // Implementation
}
```

Register in `tauri::Builder`:
```rust
.invoke_handler(tauri::generate_handler![
    start_recording,
    my_command,  // Add here
])
```

## Event Pattern (Rust → Frontend)

```rust
app.emit("transcript-update", payload)?;
```

## Thread Safety

```rust
Arc<RwLock<T>>      // Shared state across async tasks
Arc<AtomicBool>     // Simple flags
```

## Performance-Aware Logging

```rust
perf_debug!()   // Hot-path logging, zero cost in release
perf_trace!()   // Even finer-grained, eliminated in release
```